In respect to Ramadan Kareem Celebration today 2nd April, 2022 Nigerian Best Selling Author, Lawyer and Human Right Activist Reno Omokri has taken to his official twitter account to write down and question President Muhammadu Buhari on the supposed happenings in Nigeria.
The human right activist said President Muhammadu Buhari caused the increment in the price of food. With the current increase in the price of foodstuffs in the country, things have really become tough for alot of people.
Reno Omokri further mentioned other things that the President has done which is currently affecting the economy of the country.
He stated that President Muhammadu Buhari banned Crypto, increased the cost of electricity as well as caused naira to lose it’s value.
And in all these conditions, the President wishes the Muslim a Happy Ramadan and expects them to be happy. Adding that the citizens cannot farm, travel or sleep comfortably and he wants them to be happy.
In Lawyer Reno Omokri’s words:
“Dear Buhari,
You Raised Food price
You banned Crypto
You devalued Naira
You Raised the cost of electricity
You treat terrorists with levity
And you wish the Muslim Ummah a happy Ramadan?
We can’t travel, or farm, or sleep with two eyes closed. How can we be happy?”
However, there were various reactions from people after Lawyer Reno Omokri made the tweet on his official twitter account. Most people laid complaint on the recent happenings and how it’s affecting them.



